Version 3.20 (18 Nov 2022)
#Parent !Root
Changes

è	PrivateEye's user guide has been converted into StrongHelp format and now lives inside the app itself. Hello! The icon bar menu gains a "Help" menu entry to open it and the Filer's "Help" menu entry will launch it too.
è	RISC OS 5.21's extended format sprites are now used wherever possible, e.g. when loading PNGs containing alpha channels. This avoids the need to use the Tinct module which, while having provided great service for many years, is now unmaintained.
è	When in "Fit to screen" mode the viewer windows now draw a paper document style backdrop behind images. Its redraw is optimised to avoid flicker where possible.
è	A "Format" field was added to the image info window. This shows the screen mode of the display sprite and which OS versions it's compatible with.
è	The image info window's "Colours" field now shows when CMYK format sprites are detected.
è	The image info window's "Dimensions" field shows centimetres in addition to inches.
è	The chequerboard drawing code, used to indicate alpha transparency, was made common across all viewer windows. It now uses the PlotTiledSprite SpriteOp where available, in preference to Tinct's equivalent.
è	The icon bar's height is now read from the OS rather than being assumed, just in case it ever changes.
è	The Sprite alpha channel detector now treats both "all 0" and "all 255" for alpha values as indicating no alpha.
è	Sprite alpha channels and alpha masks are now identified in the image info window.
	è	Note on terminology: "Alpha channels" have alpha data inline amongst the pixels. This is the format that third party RISC OS applications used for years, including Tinct. "Alpha masks" have alpha data stored separately in the mask: a newer standard that RISC OS Select established. It's theoretically possible, but meaningless, to have both present in the same sprite.
è	The cache was rewritten to cope better in low memory situations. All open images are now requested through the cache. There's now a limit of 128 entries in the cache (= total open images). If this is a problem then set "cache.entries" to a larger value in Choices.
è	The cache size value in Choices is now shown in MBytes.

Fixes

è	Fix: Edits performed in "Fit to screen" will now refresh just the image area, not the whole window.
è	Fix: Zoom-to-point (Shift-Click) now works correctly when in "Fit to screen" mode.
è	Fix: Scale > Fit to screen now respects the cover icon bar flag.
è	Fix: Sprites which error when rendering will now, like JPEGs, draw the error message to the viewer window rather than causing a crash.
#Line
